# API and UI

## Server (`apps/server`)

- Hono routes stay thin — call `core` or adapters
- Validate request bodies with Zod
- Return JSON errors: `{ error: string, code: string }`
- CORS: allow only `localhost` origins in dev

## Web (`apps/web`)

- Fetch via typed client generated from route shapes or shared types in `core`
- Show severity badges for scan findings: error / warning / info
- Editor: warn before save if record is `writable: false`
- Never store memory content in `localStorage`

## UX priorities

1. Health Scan results — primary screen after project select
2. Session Preview — secondary panel or tab
3. Raw file browser — tertiary; collapsible

## Accessibility

- Keyboard navigable scan results list
- Sufficient contrast on severity colors
